column31: Let’s get behind this beautiful family on their quest for justice ❤️🙏🏼
column35: Mama Quaintrelle
column36:
PUBLIC SERVICE ANNOUNCEMENT: Australian Father Lindsey Day’s family vs NSW Health and the NSW Coroner. 

Lindsey was the love of Vanessas life.

He was only 39 years old.

A loving and gentle soul, a wonderful partner, a fantastic Dad, happy and most importantly, healthy. 

That all changed when he got two routine vaccinations in anticipation of his grandchild’s arrival.

Influenza and TDap (Boostrix).

Like many, many people before him, within a day of his vaccinations, Lindsey had fallen ill. The morning after sickness took hold, he took some cold and flu tablets and attempted to soldier on and get to work.

Lindsey didn’t make it to work that day. 

Unbeknownst to Vanessa, the love of her life would never make it to work again, and he would never get to meet his grandchild.

Vanessas world was turned upside down when he came back inside feeling extremely ill, his last words were that he “couldn’t breathe.” Seconds later, he collapsed right there in the house. 

Lindsey suffered a grand mal seizure (no prior history of seizures in his entire 39 years) and shortly after, went into cardiac arrest.

Vanessa performed CPR while the ambulance rushed to her aide. After Lindsey arrived at Nepean hospital in Penrith NSW, scans showed that he had suffered a catastrophic brain injury, which medical staff said was unlike anything they had ever seen before.

Sadly, at the young age of 39, Lindsey was never to regain consciousness and he died at the hospital in May 2018.

A few months after his Autopsy confirmed a cardiac episode, and after a public inquest into the cause of his death was promised, a TGA panel decided the inquest was no longer necessary, and ultimately his cause of death was CHANGED to “OLD and acute ischaemic changes in the heart” which is inconsistent with the original autopsy findings of “acute ischaemic changes in the heart in the range aged between 12 to 24 hours”.

In a perfect world, Vanessa would not be left to fight alone against a corrupt and broken system. But here we are.

https://lindseyday.org/

The family are seeking a public inquest to get the correct cause of death. 

They are requesting the vaccines Lindsey received be considered as a potential cause of death in an open court, something that has NEVER happened in Australia before. This is not a claim for damages.

As this is a coronial matter, it is not possible to find a lawyer to work on a no win-no pay basis, because even if they win the inquest, no costs are awarded, which is how lawyers get paid in no win-no pay cases. Please open the link provided for a detailed time line of events. 

The family is challenging the New South Wales Coroner’s recent decision to:

(1) change the cause of death of Lindsey Day to Coronary Artery Disease even though there is no evidence he suffered a heart attack; and

(2) cancel a previously promised public inquest into his cause of death, which was to have been held in open court.

Lindsey suffered a cardiac arrest which, to date, remains unexplained.  A cardiac arrest is not the same thing as a heart attack and the fact that the TGA and NSW Coroner are refusing Lindsey the investigation he so deserves is beyond criminal.

There’s no vaccine injury court in Australia.

There’s no government acknowledgement of genuine risks.

There’s no recourse. No warnings to follow such incidents. And no AFFORDABLE route for justice to be served.

Just the families left broken, with no one to help pick up the pieces. 

That’s where WE THE PEOPLE come in.

Please donate, SHARE, and let Lindsey’s family know you care: https://lindseyday.org/

They don’t want to see this happen to any more families. 

We stand with you Vanessa ❤️

#justiceforlindsey

column36:
CASHLESS AND NEGATIVELY INTEREST-RATED = ROBBED BY IMF

https://www.skynews.com.au/details/_6138259787001

A VERY DANGEROUS new law is about to be presented to the Senate: 
Currency (Restrictions on the Use of Cash) Bill 2019 

This bill would ban cash transactions over $10,000. If you break the rules you get two years in jail and/or pay up to $25,200 fine. 

The bill has passed the House of Representatives, were Labor voted for it. But since then many members of Parliament have woken up to it and became aware that this cash-ban would push people into the 'clutches of the banks', and restrict freedom.

The Senate reffered the bill to its References Committee where the majority opposed it and argued that the government should not be interfering with the individuals legal right to spend cash as they wish nor should the government make the use of cash a criminal offence.

However, the government insists that this legislation is intended to stamp out tax evasion (black economy). 

One issue is not generally known and gravely concerning—International Monetary Found's (IMF) proposal to introduce  negative interest rates. It all links up into what seems like a much more sinister scheme. 

By punishing people who are paying cash with jail terms, the government forces them into the clutches of the banks. 

Currently, there are five Central Banks with interest rates below zero: Japan -0.10%; Sweden -0.30%; European Central Bank -0.40%; Denmark -0.70%; and Switzerland -0.80%. With the way we are going now, our Reserve Bank might also end up having interest rates below zero. 

So where does the $10 K cash limit fit into this? Because of dreadful returns, bank deposit have been falling. Customers would hoard their money rather than stick it in the bank. This doesn't please the IMF. 

In February 2019, the IMF published a report called "Cashing in; how to make  negative interest rates work" and proposed that banks drop interest rates  to -4%. This means that people who deposit money into bank accounts would have to pay banks for keeping their money. But would YOU still deposit if you were told that it would cost you $2000 a year? I wouldn’t. 
The IMF knows this and they know well that negative interest rates won't work for banks if people continue to have cash. 

Therefore the IMF has been contemplating a range of things that can be done by Central Banks to stop people taking money out of their accounts and hoarding it under their beds. In its above-mentioned report, the IMF contemplates several measures,  among them: 
• banning cash altogether; 
• putting expiry date on notes that people take out of the ATM so they spend quickly;
• having "a serial number lottery plan" whereby each year Central Bank would pick a number between zero and nine, and all notes (paper money) ending in that number would no longer be legal tender.

These were only some of the things that IMF contemplated. 

There is an international agenda run by IMF to eliminate cash altogether. Neither the Coalition nor the Labor Party understand this. They think it's all about restricting the black economy. No politiician has read the IMF report and when they vote, they won't understand what they're really voting for.

The IMF says that they want to stimulate economies and prevent a recession with negative interest rates. The UN says that they want to save the planet with climate action. Both seem  much more like plans to  impoverish our advanced western countries, which is what Marxist Globalist are determined to achieve and take over.

column31: Re: Elderberry ... I saw this and thought it important to share for Info's sake.... I am not endorsing the contents, just sharing the info. It doesnt look like they are 100% against elderberry... just advising not to take it every day, or to at least do more research. Anyway, I know a lot of mamas use elderberry so sharing the info: "From Hear This Well Many people won't want to hear this, but did you know that using elderberry carries a risk of causing a cytokine storm? It should NOT be given out of fear of coronavirus. If you or someone you love takes elderberry every day, they need to read this. 'Stanford physician Catherine Blish has studied the hyperinflammatory response to severe influenza in pregnancy extensively attempting to understand why many pregnant women become extremely ill when exposed to influenza. She has stated that abnormally elevated chemokine levels common in pregnancy draw too many white blood cells to the lung. “That’s a bad thing in a lung where you need air space.” Getting the flu during pregnancy, especially pandemic strains such as those that caused the pandemics of 1918, 1957 and 2009, carries a heightened risk for pneumonia and death.”[ii] What she’s talking about here is a cytokine storm. The clinical presentation of the storms was first associated with the 1918 flu and included accounts of patients drowning because their lungs filled with fluid and blood. In 2013 researchers examined the lung tissue of 50 victims of 2009 H1N1 who had died of cytokine storms had “remarkably” elevated levels of IL-1 receptor antagonist protein,IL-6, tumor necrosis factor-alpha, IL-8, monocyte chemoattractant protein-1, macrophage inflammatory protein 1-beta, and interferon-inducing protein-10 [iv] which undoubtedly contributed to the over recruitment of white blood cells. These cytokine storms trigger a type of viral induced sepsis which is an autoimmune event involving an amped up immune system response that results in a fatal pneumonia. It is usually associated with H1N1, but coronaviruses have sparked storms, as well. For what it’s worth the 2019-nCoV includes a risk of what some researchers are calling Wuhan Pneumonia which seems to be caused by some sort of cytokine storm. Now let’s stop and think for a moment about what we have already read. Three of the seven cytokines I listed up above are those the crappy, cherry-picked marketing article mentioned elderberry upregulating. It gets worse for elderberry because researchers found specifically that areas of the lungs that had high bacterial infection also had high levels of IL-6, IL-8[v], so it doesn’t seem prudent to risk exacerbating that.' Read more: https://naturallysimple.org/living/2020/02/14/why-elderberry-might-not-be-the-best-adjunct/ If you want to read about Chinese herbs that stop viral replication, see here: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4032839/ Some other easy to find options: OLIVE LEAF The leaves of Olive trees (Olea europea) contain a substances called elenoic acid and calcium elonate has been identified as a powerful inhibitor of a wide range of viruses in laboratory tests., including influenza, herpes, polio and coxsackie viruses. These substances block the production of enzymes that allow viruses to replicate. PAU D’ARCO Pau d’arco (Tabebuia impetiginosa), also known as lapacho or ipe roxo, is an Amazon tree with healing inner bark that can treat colds, influenza, herpes and viral stomatis. It contains quinoids that inhibit virus replication by damaging the DNA and RNA inside the viral protein that would insert itself in a healthy human cell and replicate. What are your thoughts?

column35: Lily Nichols, RDN
column36:
VITAMIN D & PREGNANCY /// If there’s one nutrient that sticks out like a sore thumb, it’s vitamin D. We call it a vitamin, but technically, it’s a hormone. Unlike most nutrients, the major contributor to our intake is NOT food; it’s sunlight (or nowadays, supplements).⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I have a special love for vitamin D that started in my undergrad nutrition studies after I talked my way into a grad-level vitamins metabolism class. The course was taught by none other than a professor who focused much of her career on—get this—reproductive health & vitamin D.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This gave me in-depth insight into the complexities of vitamin D metabolism.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
In pregnancy, vitamin D metabolism is upregulated, resulting in what they call “supraphysiologic” levels of the active form of the vitamin. It directly affects placental function, insulin resistance, regulates genetic expression in your baby, is key to bone development, and may have long lasting effects on a child’s future risk of disease (#epigenetics), including lower risk of type 1 diabetes.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
It can also reduce the risk of many pregnancy complications, the most compelling of which is #pretermbirth. In one study, mothers with adequate levels had a 60% lower risk of preterm birth.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The research is extensive. And yet our current rec’d intake consistently fails to maintain adequate levels in mama & baby. Some researchers point the finger at a statistical error when the original vitamin D recs were set, which may have underestimated needs (for all, not just pregnancy) by a factor of 10.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Nonetheless, if you want to maintain adequate levels (in you + baby), we have multiple RCTs showing that supplementation w/ 4,000 IU is both necessary & safe.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
More research on #vitaminD can be found in Ch 6 & 9 of Real Food for Pregnancy.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
For those who *really* want a deep dive, I have a whole 90+ min webinar on this via @whnacademy. RDs: We're dropping CEUs for our courses effective March 15th; buy now so you can earn 1.5 CEUs! http://bit.ly/2TYJBwp

column36:
Sharing:

For those who may be stocking up on items for CV - I have recently read from a friend who is in the medical field, but is naturally minded and knows her stuff (she does not vaccinate, for example), that you may *not* want to use elderberry for this virus (or even in preparation for it) as it may exacerbate symptoms via upregulating cytokines and causing a cytokine storm.

This is not the first time I have read elderberry can be an issue when it comes to certain viruses! Just a heads up. 

Thankfully there are other options for fighting this if for some reason you contract it, she suggested:

Lypo-Spheric Vitamin C 
Selenium (or Brazil nuts)
Bio active silver
Baicalin (Chinese herb)
NAC (n-acetyl cysteine)

She also said to learn how to dislodge mucus from the lungs (humidifiers will come in handy).

Personally, I’d also say make sure you have magnesium, zinc, and a b complex vitamin on hand. Along with oregano essential oil and other expectorant oils.

column31: A Cure Worse Than the Disease? Peter Smith Quadrant Online 3rd March 2020 American writer H L Menken provided a perspective on scares in 1918. “Civilization, in fact, grows more and more maudlin and hysterical; especially under democracy it tends to degenerate into a mere combat of crazes; the whole aim of practical politics is to keep the populace alarmed (and hence clamorous to be led to safety) by menacing it with an endless series of hobgoblins, most of them imaginary.” Nothing has changed in the past 100 years. Right now, the “Let’s call it Trumpvirus”, as columnist Gail Collins put it in the New York Times, is sweeping the world. Hatched, no doubt, in Mar-a-Lago and the Kremlin by Trump and Putin in a collusive effort to kill off Bernie Sanders and Joe Biden. Old folks with underlying medical conditions are particularly susceptible, we’re told, and heart-attack Bernie and demented Joe are obvious targets. Or, just maybe, it happened by accident in a Chinese wet market selling all manner of unpalatable and unsavoury animals to be butchered on the spot. Ugh! Another theory of course is that it escaped from some Chinese biological warfare lab. Yes, that’s feasible, bugger a variety of deadly poxes, nothing like giving healthy adults a mild case of a flu-like virus to kill them off. I do find some respite in the wall-to wall coverage of the latest coronavirus (Covid-19). Climate change, bushfires, floods and droughts are off the front page. It is as though we have switched into an alternate universe where all our troubles have been boiled down to the latest in a long line of threatening morbidities. Each abruptly disappears leaving a temporary vacuum in the space marked “the next unnamed pandemic.” There might well, in the future, be a really deadly pandemic. Bad things can happen. But somehow, I don’t think that Covid-19 lives up to that billing. Who knows, but it will likely be contained, as have other threatening new viruses in recent decades — SARS, for example, another coronavirus which emerged also from China in 2002, and a new strain of swine flu, which was declared a pandemic in 2009. And who still remembers bird flu in 1997? As Trump suggests, we should keep our cool even if parts of the media invest in panic. Remember, the degree of panic has little to do, necessarily, with the severity of the threat. People might be trampled in rushing out of a cinema on hearing the fire alarm. Yet the fire might turn out to be of little threat. I rather liked the matter-of-fact comments of Professor Ian Mackay of the University of Queensland, as reported in The Australian. “We already have four of these coronaviruses, mostly causing colds. We get them every year.” And the reported comments in today’s paper (March 3) of UNSW virologist Peter White to the effect that the virus would degenerate into another form of the common cold once the global community became immune to it. Evolutionary theory is at play when germs and viruses emerge. Those that are mostly deadly tend to disappear quickly as the hosts die off, preventing contagion. The least deadly live on as the hosts go about their business, touching and spluttering over their fellows; as you discover on public transport. I had a cold not so long ago. After about seven or eight days of sneezing and stuffiness; as unpleasant as it is to describe, the mucus from my nose turned greenish. I immediate took a course of amoxycillin, which I keep handy in case of need. I dare say I would have recovered without it but I have become less stoical as the years go by. My point. I doubt all of those people would have died from the infamous Spanish flu in 1918-19 if the circumstances had been less crowded, the hygiene better and, critically, if antibiotics had been around to combat the secondary bacterial infections (bacterial pneumonia), which, it is now thought, mainly caused fatalities. Of course, even with modern Western medicine people die of the seasonal flu each year and have already died of Covid-19; mainly in China, though also in much smaller numbers elsewhere — notably in Iran, Italy and South Korea. But perspective is needed. The CDC estimates that about 34,000 Americans died of the flu during 2018/19. To date, as I write, six American have died from Covid-19 and one Australian. All were in the category of being susceptible to this kind of thing. No doubt many more people, particularly the aged and medically frail, will die, as they will also of all manner of respiratory illnesses. I don’t mean to minimise the threat or to seem callous about those who have and will succumb to the virus. I have no elderly parents to worry about but do have an older sister in poor health and young grandchildren. Taking personal precautions to avoid contagion is sensible, as always And given the incipient panic, it will be a relief if an effective vaccine is found and, in the meantime, if particular antiviral drugs are shown to be (truncated)

column31: Our school keep emailing out medical 'advice'. Yesterday we got this email. Since when did the MMR protect against meningitis? Or have I missed something? Meningitis Dear Anna, We have a staff member with suspected Meningitis. Meningitis is an infection of the protective membranes that surround the brain and spinal cord (meninges). It can affect anyone, but is most common in babies, young children, teenagers and young adults. Meningitis can be very serious if not treated quickly. It can cause life-threatening blood poisoning (septicaemia) and result in permanent damage to the brain or nerves. A number of vaccinations are available that offer some protection against meningitis. Symptoms of meningitis Symptoms of meningitis develop suddenly and can include: a high temperature (fever) of 38C or above being sick a headache a rash that does not fade when a glass is rolled over it (but this will not always develop) a stiff neck a dislike of bright lights drowsiness or unresponsiveness fits (seizures) These symptoms can appear in any order. You do not always get all the symptoms. When to get medical help You should get medical advice as soon as possible if you're concerned that you or your child could have meningitis. Trust your instincts and do not wait until a rash develops. Call 999 for an ambulance or go to your nearest A&E immediately if you think you or your child might be seriously ill. Call NHS 111 or your GP surgery for advice if you're not sure if it's anything serious or you think you may have been exposed to someone with meningitis. How meningitis is spread Meningitis is usually caused by a bacterial or viral infection. Bacterial meningitis is rarer but more serious than viral meningitis. Infections that cause meningitis can be spread through: sneezing coughing kissing sharing utensils, cutlery and toothbrushes Meningitis is usually caught from people who carry these viruses or bacteria in their nose or throat but are not ill themselves. It can also be caught from someone with meningitis, but this is less common. Vaccinations against meningitis Vaccinations offer some protection against certain causes of meningitis. These include the: meningitis B vaccine – offered to babies aged 8 weeks, followed by a second dose at 16 weeks and a booster at 1 year 6-in-1 vaccine – offered to babies at 8, 12 and 16 weeks of age pneumococcal vaccine – offered to babies born before 1 January 2020 at 8 and 16 weeks and 1 year of age; babies born on or after 1 January 2020 have 2 doses at 12 weeks and 1 year Hib/MenC vaccine – offered to babies at 1 year of age MMR vaccine – offered to babies at 1 year and a second dose at 3 years and 4 months meningitis ACWY vaccine – offered to teenagers, sixth formers and "fresher" students going to university for the first time Treatments for meningitis People with suspected meningitis will usually have tests in hospital to confirm the diagnosis and check whether the condition is the result of a viral or bacterial infection. Bacterial meningitis usually needs to be treated in hospital for at least a week. Treatments include: antibiotics given directly into a vein fluids given directly into a vein oxygen through a face mask Viral meningitis tends to get better on its own within 7 to 10 days and can often be treated at home. Getting plenty of rest and taking painkillers and anti-sickness medication can help relieve the symptoms in the meantime. Regards

44. Any person who -

Please support BRAVE Palmerston mum Sam Baker at Forest Parade Censorship facebook page..this is now 3rd parent I am aware of who has been issued with one, Sam and another mum from NT and now this mum in article from Tasmania.. do you know anyone else? Please see below from Forest Parade Censorship post.. https://www.facebook.com/2262613874003848/posts/2514519942146572/ It is disgusting that the Education Department are using trespass notices to shut down and shut parents up. 🤫🤐 It seems issuing trespass notices to parents is the new norm. Or even more disturbingly maybe it always was; yet we just didn’t hear about it. In almost all cases they are issued after a parent makes a complaint, in my case about non inclusion of my son, and disability discrimination. At no stage did I ever threaten, abuse or swear at any staff/students or visitors. Yet I was issued a trespass notice. Why? Because I made a complaint, a complaint they don’t want other parents learning about, hearing about, asking about most of all have them questioning if the same could of been or was occurring with their children. Why was I issued a trespass notice? Because I spoke out for my NON VERBAL son and his rights to be treated the same as his peers and most importantly BECAUSE THEY CAN! Without rhyme or reason THEY CAN issue a trespass notice on anyone at any time and they aren’t even required to supply proof and/or reasoning. So with no proof, no reasoning and without one shred of evidence ANY PARENT can be issued a trespass notice. As they say, "Power tends to corrupt, and absolute power corrupts absolutely.” Sadly, this is evident in my case with Education NT and also within the Education Department in other states. This should be a LAST RESORT, not a tool to VICTIMISE and shut down parents for addressing issues, abuse or shortfalls in their children’s education and that is exactly what trespass notices are being used for. An AVO or DVO requires proof and is meted out not by the abuser or abused but an impartial party (magistrate, police officer). In this case the trespass notice is issued by the school..... The respondent to your complaint. No independent party decides if it’s reasoned, appropriate, if there’s proof and more importantly; there is no independent review to even assess if it has any justification. It’s a disgusting abuse of power by the same hands and minds we entrust the care of our children to!

column31: [ ](https://mewe.com/group/5b31cb47a5f4e56a69075d2d/profile/5acd7fa884162152af0af665)📷 [Sarah Lowrey[](https://mewe.com/group/5b31cb47a5f4e56a69075d2d/profile/5acd7fa884162152af0af665)WAKE THE FLOCK UP!](https://mewe.com/group/5b31cb47a5f4e56a69075d2d) 2 days ago mewe Photo album: #doctors who bully Are Doctors Giving Patients Up-to-Date Vaccine Safety Information (or Any Safety Information at All)?*********************************************************In 1986, Congress passed the National Childhood Vaccine Injury Act (NCVIA), a carefully crafted piece of legislation that gave vaccine manufacturers their dream come true: blanket immunity from liability for injuries resulting from childhood vaccines. Throwing a bone to the safety concerns of consumers, the Act also mandated that the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) (via the CDC) develop and distribute educational materials to inform vaccine recipients and/or their parents about a given vaccine’s risks and benefits. The NCVIA stipulated that doctors give out the appropriate materials—currently called Vaccine Information Statements (VISs)—“prior to every dose of specific vaccines,” including before “each dose of a multi-dose series.” Early on, government documentation emphasized the importance of giving VISs every time a vaccine is administered because “the health status of the child could have changed”—and as an example of changes in health status, the CDC cited children with “evolving neurological disorder[s].” By 2005, however, researchers were calling attention to doctors’ frequent failure to give out VISs, while also noting that the physicians who did distribute VISs “rarely initiated discussions regarding contraindications to immunizations.” To rectify the situation, the same authors carried out a CDC-coordinated evaluation in 2007 and proposed revisions “that would alert the physician to the need to use the VIS.” Neither the CDC nor state-level officials endorsed the proposed revisions. When it comes to their duty to educate, all signs indicate that doctors and the CDC are falling down on the job. At present, few researchers are even asking whether doctors comply with their legal responsibility to not only distribute vaccine-specific VISs each time but also give recipients “an opportunity to ask questions about the vaccine.” Nor does anyone appear to be investigating whether health care providers check in with parents about changes in a child’s health status, or whether providers are aware of VIS updates. When it comes to their duty to educate, all signs indicate that doctors and the CDC are falling down on the job. Dumbing down the content Post-NCVIA, researchers were quick to laud VISs as “revolutionary” tools for provider-patient education. However, the government has dumbed down the content and process requirements for the vaccine education materials several times since 1986. Currently, instead of the comprehensive 12-page pamphlets only offered for a short while in the early 1990s (which responded to ten very explicit NCVIA requirements), parents receive “concise” front-and-back one-pagers (or their electronic equivalent) that are only expected to cover four “general” areas: vaccine benefits and risks (brief descriptions), a “statement” about the National Vaccine Injury Compensation Program (NVICP) and “other relevant information.” In 2008, the CDC also introduced “pediatric multi-vaccine” VISs, ostensibly to “reduce parents’ reading load” at doctors’ visits where children were routinely receiving as many as nine vaccines in one sitting. How did the agency collapse information from five separate VISs (for the DTaP, polio, hepatitis B, pneumococcal conjugate and Haemophilus influenzae type b vaccines) into a single two-page document? It eliminated “some ‘nice to know’ information” and condensed remarks about the NVICP and the Vaccine Adverse Event Reporting System (VAERS)—the two key resources important to know about in the event of an adverse reaction—down to the bare minimum. Slipping in more changes Vaccine Information Statements typically list a handful of categories of people who “should not get” the vaccine. For most vaccines, this includes individuals who had a life-threatening allergic reaction to a previous dose of the vaccine or who are severely allergic to one of the vaccine’s ingredients. However, parents who want to know what a vaccine’s ingredients are (so that they can assess allergy risks) must take additional steps to find out, because the VISs do not list the ingredients. Instead, the VIS advises parents to “Ask your health care provider if you want information about vaccine components.” Other categories of people who should not get vaccines, as per most VISs, include individuals with weakened immune systems (due to disease or medical treatments), women who are pregnant or “might be pregnant” (the CDC (truncated)

column31: While coronavirus' political madness is spreading in Italy, some strange characters - politicians and journalists - thought it'd be a clever idea to bring us up in the middle of the pandemic, so we had to clarify our position. We are not NoVax or Anti-vax, as we consider labels to be foolish, we are against any mandatory medical treatment and we claim the right to say No, because this is what Freedom of choice means! That being said, we needed to express our thoughts on the present situation mostly because our country is in the grip of political madness. Some examples? Let's talk about the number of cases you read in the newspapers: well, know that they are not real. We have 3 sources to access the information on the confirmed cases in Italy: first is the sum total of data from single Regions;next is the Higher Institute of Health that is the source communicating with the WHO; last we have the press. Now, to date 1st of March 2020, we go from 1694 positive cases to 488 cases confirmed by the Higher Institute of Health, with 34 presumed deaths for coronavirus (presumed as we don't know whether they died because of the coronavirus or of other pathologies) and in all these numbers we know that about 50% of cases have very light symptoms or no symptoms at all. Another example of italian madness? The advisor to our Ministry of Health for the management of coronavirus emergency, who is now a member of the WHO, had resigned from the Higher Institute of Health after accusations of conflicts of interest, especially related to pharmaceutical companies' advisory, deriving from the press (like for meningococcus vaccine…). Let's be clear, it is not all bad in Italy, we have an excellent national healthcare system with great doctors, nurses and health operators who are acting in the best possible way, but as soon as we look over those who get their hands dirty with daily work, we feel discouraged. Management inability at a national level surrounded by a so-called scientific community which is still debating to understand whether we will all die or it is just a flu-like virus. This is the situation in Italy and this is what we think of it: WHERE ARE THE ANTI-VAXXERS? Don’t worry, they are all here, watching you plumbing the depths of absurdity Just a matter of few days and all those who should have felt reassured after the triumphant war to introduce 10 mandatory vaccines, found themselves defenceless discovering -oh my! the existence of more viruses than just varicella! Corvelva Papers #4 - #stayhuman

column35: Maya
column36:
I will NEVER be bullied or harassed into silence!

This week alone I’ve had numerous people tell me that I can’t reference Martin Luther King Jr. or Rosa Parks because I am not black. And that it’s inappropriate for me to use their quotes in relation to the Medical Freedom Movement. 

That is the most ridiculous thing I’ve ever heard. 

First of all, if you don’t like racism why are you perpetuating it by telling a white person that they can’t reference a great leader of a movement because they’re not of the same race? That’s racism. So don’t perpetuate what you don’t want to see in the world.￼

Second of all, if you don’t see how the Medical Freedom movement is a civil rights issue you don’t know enough about the topic to be commenting on what I’m doing. ￼

I’ll say again what I told these people, I am not the enemy here. 

The pharmaceutical companies are and our governmental agencies are. They are the ones that conducted the Tuskegee experiment on black people. They are the ones that hide and destroyed the data proving that African-American boys are at a higher risk for autism when receiving the MMR before a certain age. 

Direct your anger towards the correct entities. 

Join us in the fight for Medical Freedom because this fight includes and involves all races, all people, all economic statuses-everyone. ￼

And finally, using these great leaders for inspiration does not in any way, shape or form mean that I am comparing what happened to African-American people in our country to the situation we are all facing with these vaccine mandates. ￼

But I am RELATING one civil rights movement to another because there are similarities, namely unwarranted discrimination and segregation. ￼

Yes I am a white person but I am not white washing or using white privilege to “get likes on Facebook.” I’m just a person and I am fully allowed to reference whoever the fuck I want to from the past. ￼👊

I fight alongside people of all races in this movement-Hispanic, Asian, black, THIS EFFECTS ALL PEOPLE. ￼

If we can’t learn from our past and draw inspiration from it and talk about it and reference it, we are doomed to repeat it￼. 

I don’t know about you but I don’t want to repeat any of the dark chapters of human history but we are going in that direction currently so instead of bickering amongst each other I suggest we come together and fight this madness. ￼

#itsyourfighttoo
#medicalfreedom
#joinus

column35: Pete
column36:
'Engineering Infectious cDNAs of Coronavirus as Bacterial Artificial Chromosomes' - 2016 

"The large size of the coronavirus (CoV) genome (around 30 kb) and the instability in bacteria of plasmids carrying CoV replicase sequences, represent serious restrictions for the development of CoV infectious clones using reverse genetic systems similar to those used for smaller positive sense RNA viruses. To overcome these problems, several approaches have been established in the last thirteen years. Here we describe the engineering of CoV full-length cDNA clones as bacterial artificial chromosomes (BACs), using the Middle East respiratory syndrome CoV (MERS-CoV) as a model."

"the development of CoV infectious clones provides a valuable molecular tool to study fundamental viral processes, to develop genetically defined vaccines, and to test antiviral drugs." 

"The BAC approach, originally applied to the transmissible gastroenteritis coronavirus (TGEV), has been successfully used to engineer the infectious clones of the feline infectious peritonitis virus (FIPV) and the human CoVs (HCoVs) HCoV-OC43, SARS-CoV and MERS-CoV, and it is potentially applicable to the cloning of other CoV cDNAs, other viral genomes, and large-size RNAs of biological relevance."

https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4726977/

This is Argentina. 
All our countries may end this way, because every single day they try to erode our rights, the right to decide of our bodies, the right to take care of our kids the way we want to and the fundamental right to be free.
We are seeing it in these days, with the panic created by media around the coronavirus disease, used as a weapon to weaken our freedom.
We must support all the countries that live under threat: our presence in Munich is really necessary to stay strong and to show that WE WILL NEVER GIVE UP and for sure WE WILL NOT COMPLY.

#MunichMarch21
#FreedomOfChoice
#MyBodyMyChoice
#MedicalFreedom

Vaccines in ARGENTINA

In Argentina, there is a movement of citizens concerned about the safety of vaccines.  But we are not as much as we need to be.  We have not, yet, managed to create an association. Because of the many obstacles and lacking of resources and support.

Most citizens are ignorant of the danger. Many are afraid.  Here, vaccines are not only mandatory; it’s illegal to live without vaccines. We are under legal violence of the judges and the government.  They threat parents with taking away their parental rights and authority. Taking away the children from the family to vaccinate by force.
Homeschooling in many places is illegal, also.
Our own family, neighbors, and health care providers can turn us in.!!!

Many families choose to hide.  Others choose to vaccinate, even knowing the poison in them.  A few had left the country.

This is a very scary time here.  

Unfortunately, lawyers don’t find a course of action.  They say there’s no judge in our side.  

In Argentina, we went from having 6 to 19 mandatory vaccines during the first two years of life, in just a decade. With many doses of each.  

Until December 2018, we had an obsolete national vaccination law, inherited from the military dictatorship. 

Far from advancing in the conquest of individual liberties, respect free consent and the exercise of the autonomy of freedom, the new vaccination law toughened legislation.  It was approved unanimously WITHOUT DEBATE for all our “representatives” at the Congress, at the end of December of the year 2018.  Due to this law, health care providers have lost value and authority.  They became just employees of the pharmaceutical industry.

Vaccines will be required to renew ID, get a driver's license, passport.  They are still not doing this.
But they are asking every child has all the vaccines without any exemption.  There are no religious, philosophical, or medical exemptions.
Access to social security benefits was subject to vaccination, as well.

In October, the digital vaccination card system is already functioning.  This means that to be vaccinated we have to give our ID and they will record our medical file in the computer. This is a “pharmaceutical tyranny”, as Robert Kennedy jr. described.  

In 2018 they justified, for two cases of measles, a campaign to apply extra doses of MMR between 12 months and 5 years. By 5 years our children had three doses of MMR.
Now they are vaccinating children aged 6 to 12 months because 20 measles cases. Which is contraindicated in the insert of the vaccine.

Total cases of measles in 2019 were less than a hundred.  No death was reported.

There is a surveillance reporting system called ESAVI but doctors and nurses do not report adverse effects.
There is not a compensation program for the victims. 

There are no reliable statistics in our country.  Therefore, they say quantities of ill people and death without any proof.  However, nobody is questioning.  Media is completely censored. The media is totally denying us the right to speak.

In classrooms and in doctor's offices, there’s an increasing incidence of autism and other neurological, neurolinguistics and motor disorders; of chronic and autoimmune diseases, childhood cancer, allergies of all kinds, especially food and respiratory, asthma, type 1 diabetes.

We suspect the existence of conflicts of interest of our public health officials, because of their history of ties with vaccine manufacturing laboratories.

Doctors, in the University, do not receive training on vaccines and are not trained to detect and report adverse effects.

Doctors and teachers have to report the vaccination status of children.  They have become police officers and executioners of the government without mediating the exercise of their conscientious objection or their professional judgment.

In rural areas, health promoters in general are illiterate people, trained to give injections and receive monetary rewards for applying vaccines.

In 2014, GSK was found guilty by the Argentine government for killing 14 babies in a medical vaccine experiment.  Testing Syflorix, a vaccine for pneumonia.
GSK was fined for a sum of 1,000,000 Argentine pesos (120,000 dollars) only for not giving proper informed consent.  Nobody in prison for that.  No further investigations of the deaths.

column36:
IMPORTANT ANNOUNCEMENT - CORONAVIRUS
1. If you have a runny nose and sputum, you MAY have a common cold/flu it isn't necessarily that you've caught the virus
2. .The term pneumonia describes the swelling of lung tissue. It’s usually caused by a bacterial infection, and has been seen in Covid-19 patients. One of the most common symptoms of Covid-19 is a dry cough
3. Because the virus is relatively new, there’s a lot not known about it, like the temperatures it can withstand.so early after the discovery of the virus. What we can do is look at related viruses. Coronavirus is a family of viruses including the common cold, SARS, and SARS-CoV-2
4.It’s difficult to say exactly how far droplets spread when you sneeze, as it depends on a factors like humidity and temperature. Research in recent years has shown that droplets from sneezes have the potential to spread several metres from the sneezing person. 
5The WHO says “Studies suggest that coronaviruses (including preliminary information on the COVID-19 virus) may persist on surfaces for a few hours or up to several days.
6. On fabric it may survive for some hours. normal laundry detergent will kill it.
7.you should avoid drinking liquids with ice..
8. Wash your hands frequently as the virus can live on your hands for 5-10 minutes, but - a lot can happen during that time - you can rub your eyes, pick your nose unwittingly and so on.
9. Gargling with salt water is recommended by the NHS for adults who have a sore throat, but only to relieve symptoms once you have caught it, not as a preventative measure.
10. Can't emphasise enough - drink plenty of water!
THE SYMPTOMS
1.It will first infect the throat, so you may have a sore throat lasting 3/4 days
2. The virus can blend into a nasal fluid that enters the trachea and then the lungs, causing pneumonia. This takes about 5/6 days further.
3. With the pneumonia comes high fever and difficulty in breathing.
4.In general, 1-3 are roughly an accurate description of the common symptoms of Covid-19, although some patients may experience other symptoms and the timing of those symptoms may differ.
The CDC (Centre for Disease Control) says that sore throat has been reported “in some patients”. More commonly, symptoms include fever, a cough, muscle pain and shortness of breath, as the post claims. Not everyone who has Covid-19 will get pneumonia though. The NHS does not mention nasal congestion that ‘feels like drowning’ as a specific symptom for Covid-19.

It does advise that you use its 111 online coronavirus service, your doctor but don't visit 

SPREAD THE WORD - PLEASE  SHARE.AND ALSO SEE RECENT UPDATES FROM NHS AND ELSEWHERE AND
HELP PREVENT THE SPREAD OF THE VIRUS BECAUSE
when it comes to health, everyone wants what's best for themselves and their families. See the latest information from the National Health Service (NHS) so you can help prevent the spread of the coronavirus (COVID-19)

column35: Purple Promise
column36:
This is Lauren’s Story, she’s one of many Gardasil victims. 

**Video in the comments**

"On November 22, 2016 our lives were changed forever. My healthy 13 year old was given a flu and HPV vaccination. I declined the HPV shot 4 times because I had a bad feeling about it and had read about healthy teens developing autoimmune diseases following this particular shot. We were told (by our pediatrician) nothing like that ever happens & that those girls were already going to get sick. “You can’t believe anything you read on the internet”, she said. My pediatrician insisted that she would get throat cancer from kissing if I did not give her this vaccine. I was NOT given INFORMED CONSENT, and will regret letting them give my daughter the Gardasil 9 shot for the rest of my life. After pulling her medical records I learned it was her 37th injection and the 51st vaccine that had been put into her body since birth. 

Before the shot, Lauren was an elite athlete and an honor student. She played soccer on a highly competitive, regional level soccer team. She also played tennis, guitar, was active in our church, straight A student, and was a member of the national junior honor society. She had big dreams and a bright future ahead of her.�
After the shot, Lauren had an adverse reaction. She developed chronic fatigue and head-pain...every second of every day. She also told me, "Mom", my brain isn't working right". She was trying to keep count of reps she was doing for a training exercise and her brain was unable to remember the numbers. She was diagnosed with mitochondria damage and still struggles with her short-term memory and processing information. Her headaches are usually between a 5-8. Ten being the most pain you can imagine or for example a bear tears your arm off. Nothing takes her pain away, not even prescription meds. We have tried everything under the sun these past 3 years to try to heal her body. She says the fatigue bothers her the worst. I asked her what it felt like and she said its like she hasn't slept in 500 days. The vaccine also triggered her body to launch an attack on itself. At one point her ANA (Antinuclear Antibody) levels were 1:1280, which is an extremely alarming rate. She has since developed autoimmunity of her thyroid and it is likely that she will continue to develop multiple autoimmune disorders because of her reaction. She now has a 500% increased risk of cancer (based on studies) because of the cell damage she has endured. �
Lauren can no longer participate in any sports or extra activities. She can't even play the guitar anymore because it makes her head hurt worse and her brain doesn't function like it used to. Heat and physical activities make her feel worse as well. She had to stop taking the advanced classes that she would have taken.�
Her treatment and recovery plan are the focus of our daily lives. Hundreds of doctors appointments, blood test, scans, IV infusions, pills, supplements, and the extra burden of eating an organic diet that is free of gluten, dairy & refined sugar are just some of the things we continue to do to try to restore her health. We are grateful that her last  ANA tests were negative. There are no days off when trying to heal from a vaccine injury. I will never stop defending her health.�
I have learned a lot these past few years. Nothing is one size fits all. My daughter is compound heterozygous for 2 SNP’s of the MTHFR gene. Because of this, she has methylation & detox deficiencies which put her at a high risk for vaccine reactions. Unfortunately, I didn't learn about this until it was too late. Watching your child's health and life be taken from them is soul crushing. This has affected our entire family and I am still grieving for the life that she once had. 

If we are not given the right to choose what medical procedures are best for our families, then we are not living in a free land. Everything that Lauren has developed is a listed side-effect (on the package insert from the manufacturer) of the Gardasil vaccine. I had concerns that I addressed with my pediatrician that day, and I was told nothing like that ever happens. Parents deserve informed consent. Where there is a risk, there must be a choice. Thank you for taking to time to read Lauren's story.

At the time we were interviewed for the VAXXED documentary I thought she was goin to recover with help from the IV infusions. However, when she went back to school and tried to play sports, her symptoms came back and then we learned about the autoimmunity. This is pretty common because autoimmune issues take several months or even years to develop after damage has occurred.

Today, Lauren continues to suffers from chronic fatigue, chronic head pain & short-term memory problems. She has also been diagnosed with autoimmunity to her thyroid, metabolic dysfunction & immune dysfunction since having the adverse reaction. She is able to attend school, but it’s much harder than (truncated)
